text:
Whether you’re living in a rental or just have trouble committing to a single style, temporary wallpaper is the solution. These 5 bold prints make the perfect accent wall or backsplash, and when you’re tired of the look you can remove the wallpaper without leaving a sticky residue behind.

1) Blue Florentine Tile

This blue and gold Florentine tile patterned wallpaper has a coastal vibe that’s perfect for beach homes. Customers loved how easy it was to peel the paper off and adhere it again when they ran into bubbles, and how forgiving the pattern was if they didn’t feel like re-positioning the paper.

2) Palm Leaves

This bright green palm leaf print wallpaper is a great choice for adding a tropical statement wall to any room. The temporary wallpaper can also be used as a drawer liner for a surprising pop of color.

3) White Brick

If you dream of living in a sunny urban loft, this white brick peel and stick wallpaper will give you city vibes without major commitment. The neutral color works well with a variety of décor while adding textural interest to any room.

4) Carrara Marble

The marble trend isn’t going away any time soon, and this Carrara marble look temporary wallpaper is perfect for furniture DIYS. It’s also a great quick fix for covering a dated kitchen backsplash while you save for renovations.

5) Watercolor Floral

Floral wallpaper is making a serious comeback—and your grandma says, “I told you so.” This lovely pink and blue watercolor floral wallpaper has a large-scale pattern that suits accent walls.
title: 5 temporary wallpapers commitment-phobes should try
